Here , the authors studied the role of a basic <termsem="GO:0031497"> chromatin assembly </term> factor ( CAF-1 ) in mouse embryonic stem cells and early embryos .
Surprisingly , they show that CAF-1 confers epigenetic information to specific genomic regions .
In addition , this study revealed that CAF-1 is required for the proper <termsem="GO:0050000"> spatial organization of chromosomes </term> in the nucleus .
This new knowledge may contribute to better understanding the role of chromatin in the maintenance of embryonic stem cell identity and plasticity .
