Further analysis by light microscopy using immunofluorescence ( IF ) allowed us to compare wild-type and p150CAF-1-depleted embryos .
A loss of p150CAF-1 staining could not be detected before the eight-cell stage ( unpublished data ) suggesting that maternally contributed protein is present in the embryo up to the four-cell stage .
